Description: "The Old Angler” Classic Italian Briefcase With Genuine Florentine Tanned Buffalo Leather Buy with Class and Confidence. Beauty, Craftsmanship and Durability - to meet your work and travel in style with this exquisite Italian handcrafted full grain leather briefcase. Leather is treated by centuries old Florentine techniques of vegetable tanning to preserve the natural beauty of the hide (see description below). The Old Angler is a collector's item. I am selling my Old Angler Collections. Features High quality leather - Genuine Florentine Tanned Buffalo Leather Artisanal craftsmanship from a renowned family owned business in Italy Beautiful geometric front lock Exterior is rich, mahogany brown with a glossy finish Interior has two well-sized compartments Golden hardware gives this briefcase a real touch of class 15.5" x 5" x 11"Imported Briefcase 1002 The antique art of vegetable tanning dates back to prehistoric Tuscany, where it has been passed on for centuries from father to son as artisan tradition. Vegetable tanning is the process by which the animal skin, or rawhide, is converted into non-degradable leather through the use of natural vegetable extracts. All of Old Angler’s leather comes from the Conceria il Gabbiano, one of Tuscany’s most qualified “concerie” or leather tanneries, where experienced artisans oversee the tanning of the leather. The Conceria il Gabbiano is part of the Consorzio Vera Pelle Italiana Conciata al Vegetale and guarantees the production of a high-quality leather that is completely natural, unique and durable. The vegetable tanning process, in which the famous 'vachetta' or Florentine leather is created, is completed in three long and complicated phases.
